{# templates/roadmaps/real-state/real-estate-market-risk.html.twig #}
{% extends 'base-roadmaps.html.twig' %}

{% block stylesheets %}
    {{ parent() }}
    {{ encore_entry_link_tags('real_state_css') }}
{% endblock %}

{% block javascripts %}
    {{ parent() }}
    {{ encore_entry_script_tags('real_state_js') }}
{% endblock %}

{% block body %}
    <div class="container">
        <!-- Article Hero -->
        <div class="article-hero animate" style="background: linear-gradient(135deg, #2f2a24 0%, #5e4b3f 100%);">
            <div class="hero-content">
                <div class="hero-icon" style="background-color: var(--real-estate-color);">
                    <i class="fas fa-chart-line"></i>
                </div>
                <h1>Market Risk <span>Understanding Real Estate Cycles</span></h1>
                <p class="hero-description">
                    Real estate markets don't move in straight lines. Learn to recognize the four phases of the cycle, avoid buying at the peak, and protect your portfolio from downturns.
                </p>
                <div class="phase-tag" style="background-color: rgba(225,112,85,0.2); color: #f7b9a9;">
                    <i class="fas fa-layer-group"></i> Phase 2: Risk Management · 8 min read
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>

        <!-- Introduction -->
        <section class="animate">
            <h2 class="section-title">🔄 The Rhythm of Real Estate</h2>
            <p style="font-size: 1.2rem; margin-bottom: 20px;">
                Just like the economy, real estate markets move in cycles. Understanding where we are in the cycle can help you
                <strong>avoid overpaying, time your purchases better, and sleep soundly during downturns.</strong>
                Let's explore the four phases every investor should know.
            </p>
        </section>

        <!-- The Four Phases (using rule-grid) -->
        <div class="rule-grid animate">
            <div class="rule-item">
                <h4><i class="fas fa-rocket"></i> Expansion</h4>
                <p>Rising demand, new construction, increasing rents and prices. Optimism grows. Often the longest phase.</p>
            </div>
            <div class="rule-item">
                <h4><i class="fas fa-mountain"></i> Peak</h4>
                <p>Prices max out, overbuilding may occur, demand slows. The market is “frothy” – be cautious.</p>
            </div>
            <div class="rule-item">
                <h4><i class="fas fa-arrow-down"></i> Contraction</h4>
                <p>Prices fall, vacancies rise, construction halts. Fear sets in. Also called the “bust” phase.</p>
            </div>
            <div class="rule-item">
                <h4><i class="fas fa-chart-line"></i> Trough / Recovery</h4>
                <p>Market bottoms out, then slowly stabilizes. Smart investors start buying.</p>
            </div>
        </div>

        <!-- Deeper Dive Card -->
        <div class="card animate">
            <h3><i class="fas fa-clock"></i> Why Cycles Matter</h3>
            <p>Buying at the peak can mean years of negative equity and poor returns. Buying in the trough can supercharge your wealth. But timing the market perfectly is impossible – the key is to <strong>average in, hold long term, and avoid panic selling.</strong></p>
            <p style="background: var(--light-gray); padding: 15px; border-radius: 12px;">
                <strong>Historical note:</strong> Since 1990, the US has seen three major cycles: the early 90s slump, the 2000s boom/bust, and the post‑2009 recovery. Each lasted roughly 7–10 years from trough to peak.
            </p>
        </div>

        <!-- Interactive Tool: Real Estate Cycle Simulator (disabled for non-logged-in) -->
        <div class="card animate" id="cycle-simulator">
            <h3><i class="fas fa-chart-simple"></i> Interactive: Real Estate Cycle Simulator</h3>
            <p>See how buying at different points in a typical 18‑year cycle affects your home's value over 20 years.</p>

            <div style="display: flex; flex-wrap: wrap; gap: 20px; margin: 20px 0;">
                <div style="flex: 1 1 200px;">
                    <label>Purchase Year in Cycle <span id="purchaseYearVal">5</span></label>
                    <input type="range" id="purchaseYear" min="0" max="17" value="5" step="1" class="cat-input" style="width:100%;">
                    <small>0 = trough, 8 = peak, 17 = late contraction</small>
                </div>
                <div style="flex: 1 1 200px;">
                    <label>Initial Home Value ($) <span id="initialValueVal">300000</span></label>
                    <input type="range" id="initialValue" min="100000" max="1000000" value="300000" step="10000" class="cat-input" style="width:100%;">
                </div>
            </div>

            <div style="margin-top: 20px;">
                <button id="simulateCycle" class="btn-outline">Simulate</button>
            </div>

            <div id="cycleResult" style="margin-top: 25px; padding: 20px; background: var(--light-color); border-radius: 12px;">
                <p>Adjust the values and click the button.</p>
            </div>

            <p class="pro-tip" style="margin-top: 15px;">
                <i class="fas fa-lightbulb"></i> This simulation uses a simplified sine‑wave model of real estate cycles. Actual markets are influenced by interest rates, employment, and many other factors. Use it to understand the concept, not to predict the future.
            </p>
        </div>

        <!-- Risk Mitigation Strategies -->
        <div class="card animate">
            <h3><i class="fas fa-shield"></i> How to Protect Yourself</h3>
            <ul>
                <li><strong>Don't try to time the market</strong> – invest consistently over time.</li>
                <li><strong>Maintain a long‑term horizon</strong> – ride out downturns.</li>
                <li><strong>Keep a cash reserve</strong> – to cover expenses if rents drop or vacancies rise.</li>
                <li><strong>Diversify across markets and property types</strong> – not all areas cycle together.</li>
                <li><strong>Avoid excessive leverage</strong> – high debt magnifies losses in a downturn.</li>
            </ul>
        </div>

        <!-- Quiz Section -->
        {% if app.user and quiz is defined and quiz %}
            {# Logged in user – quiz already taken #}
            <div class="quiz-container animate" style="background: #2f2a24;">
                <h3 style="color:white; margin-top: 0;">🧠 You've already taken this quiz</h3>
                <p style="color: #e2e8f0; font-size: 1.2rem;">
                    Your score: <strong>{{ quiz.quizzScore }}%</strong>
                </p>
                <p style="color: #cbd5e0;">
                    You can retake the quiz to improve your score. Click the button below to reset it.
                </p>
                <div class="quiz-actions">
                    <a href="{{ path('app_page_show', { journey: 'real-state', slug: 'real-estate-market-risk', retake: 1 }) }}"
                       class="btn"
                       style="background-color: #e17055; color: white; text-decoration: none;">
                        Retake Quiz
                    </a>
                </div>
            </div>
        {% else %}
            {# Show quiz (interactivity blocked by JS if not logged in) #}
            <div class="quiz-container animate" data-page-id="{{ page.id }}" style="background: #2f2a24;">
                <h3 style="color:white; margin-top: 0;">📝 Test Your Knowledge: Market Risk & Cycles</h3>

                <div class="quiz-question">1. What are the four phases of a typical real estate cycle?</div>
                <div class="quiz-options" data-question="1">
                    <div class="quiz-option" data-answer="correct">Expansion, Peak, Contraction, Trough</div>
                    <div class="quiz-option" data-answer="wrong">Boom, Bubble, Crash, Recovery</div>
                    <div class="quiz-option" data-answer="wrong">Spring, Summer, Fall, Winter</div>
                    <div class="quiz-option" data-answer="wrong">Growth, Stagnation, Decline, Rebound</div>
                </div>

                <div class="quiz-question">2. Why is buying at the peak risky?</div>
                <div class="quiz-options" data-question="2">
                    <div class="quiz-option" data-answer="wrong">Mortgages are hard to get</div>
                    <div class="quiz-option" data-answer="correct">Prices may fall soon, leading to negative equity</div>
                    <div class="quiz-option" data-answer="wrong">Rental demand is highest</div>
                    <div class="quiz-option" data-answer="wrong">Interest rates are always lowest</div>
                </div>

                <div class="quiz-question">3. What typically happens to prices during the contraction phase?</div>
                <div class="quiz-options" data-question="3">
                    <div class="quiz-option" data-answer="correct">They decline</div>
                    <div class="quiz-option" data-answer="wrong">They stabilize</div>
                    <div class="quiz-option" data-answer="wrong">They rise slowly</div>
                    <div class="quiz-option" data-answer="wrong">They skyrocket</div>
                </div>

                <div class="quiz-question">4. Which of the following is a good strategy to mitigate market risk?</div>
                <div class="quiz-options" data-question="4">
                    <div class="quiz-option" data-answer="wrong">Using maximum leverage</div>
                    <div class="quiz-option" data-answer="wrong">Buying only at peaks</div>
                    <div class="quiz-option" data-answer="correct">Maintaining a cash reserve</div>
                    <div class="quiz-option" data-answer="wrong">Ignoring market conditions</div>
                </div>

                <div class="quiz-question">5. True or False: Real estate cycles are perfectly predictable.</div>
                <div class="quiz-options" data-question="5">
                    <div class="quiz-option" data-answer="wrong">True</div>
                    <div class="quiz-option" data-answer="correct">False</div>
                </div>

                <div class="quiz-actions">
                    <button id="quiz-submit" class="btn" style="background-color: var(--real-estate-color);">Get score & submit</button>
                </div>
                <div class="quiz-result"></div>
            </div>
        {% endif %}

        <!-- Next Steps in Phase 2 -->
        <section style="margin: 60px 0;">
            <h2 class="section-title" style="text-align: center;">📘 Continue Phase 2: Risk Management</h2>
            <div class="next-steps">
                <a href="{{ path('app_page_show', { journey: 'real-state', slug: 'hidden-costs' }) }}" class="next-card">
                    <i class="fas fa-wrench"></i>
                    <h3>The Hidden Costs of Homeownership</h3>
                    <p>Taxes, insurance, maintenance – the true cost of owning.</p>
                </a>
                <a href="{{ path('app_page_show', { journey: 'real-state', slug: 'vacancy-risk' }) }}" class="next-card">
                    <i class="fas fa-door-open"></i>
                    <h3>Vacancy Risk</h3>
                    <p>How to minimize empty units and lost income.</p>
                </a>
                <a href="{{ path('app_page_show', { journey: 'real-state', slug: 'legal-liability' }) }}" class="next-card">
                    <i class="fas fa-gavel"></i>
                    <h3>Legal & Liability Risks</h3>
                    <p>Insurance, LLCs, and protecting your assets.</p>
                </a>
            </div>
        </section>
    </div>
{% endblock %}
